theorem dense_of_dense_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior (A : Set X)) → Dense (A : Set X) := by
  classical
  intro hDenseInt
  -- Express the density of `interior A` as a closure equality.
  have hEqInt : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    (Topology.dense_iff_closure_eq_univ (A := interior (A : Set X))).1 hDenseInt
  -- `closure (interior A)` is contained in `closure A` by monotonicity.
  have hIncl : closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A)
  -- Hence `closure A` must also be `univ`.
  have hEqA : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro _; trivial
    ·
      have : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
        simpa [hEqInt] using hIncl
      exact this
  -- Rewrite the equality as the desired density statement.
  exact (Topology.dense_iff_closure_eq_univ (A := A)).2 hEqA

theorem dense_of_dense_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior (A : Set X)) → Dense (A : Set X) := by
  intro hDenseInt x
  have hx : (x : X) ∈ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := hDenseInt x
  have hIncl : closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A)
  exact hIncl hx
